Date: 0/0/1991
Source: Off the Sheep's Back
Author: RICHARDS
Vol / Page: 58
Edition:
Quote: The first operation when starting a bush job is to do the scrubbing (cutting the small undergrowth, supplejack, kiekie and vines) with a slasher. A day's scrubbing will usually clear enough to keep a man chopping for a week, although it varies according to the type of country.
